The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Truck amok kills boy, woman

 A STAFF REPORTER

 A five-year-old boy and a woman in her mid-20s died and two men were injured in a road accident in Belgachhia on Sunday afternoon.

 Police said a truck lost control and rammed into a parked tempo on JK Ghosh Road. The woman and the child, identified as Subratan Bibi and Anas, were caught between the two vehicles and crushed to death.

 The injured, Sheikh Amir Ali and Sheikh Gulam, both in in their 70s, were admitted to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where their condition was stated to be critical.

 The truck driver has been arrested and the vehicle impounded. Local residents tried to set the truck on fire, but timely intervention by police prevented any untoward incident. The accident would not have occurred had there been traffic policemen, said Ramesh Shaw, a local resident.




